00:11:48,800 --> 00:11:50,960
where you've seen this house from the front.

264
00:11:50,960 --> 00:11:53,520
That's one way of viewing the house,

265
00:11:53,520 --> 00:11:56,720
one literal angle or perspective

266
00:11:56,720 --> 00:11:58,320
from which you can view the house.

267
00:11:58,320 --> 00:12:00,400
You might also see the house from the back.

268
00:12:00,400 --> 00:12:02,320
That's a different perspective,

269
00:12:02,320 --> 00:12:04,880
a different mode of presentation of the house,

270
00:12:04,880 --> 00:12:07,760
a different way that the house could be presented to you.

271
00:12:07,760 --> 00:12:10,880
And you can know the house in both of these ways

272
00:12:10,880 --> 00:12:13,200
without actually knowing that they're the same house.

273
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:15,600
And then it might be informative to you to find out,

274
00:12:15,600 --> 00:12:17,840
oh, look at that, that's the same one house.

275
00:12:17,840 --> 00:12:19,280
That's what Frege is getting at

276
00:12:19,280 --> 00:12:21,120
with this idea of a mode of presentation.

277
00:12:21,120 --> 00:12:24,880
There are two different ways of knowing Sean Carter.

278
00:12:24,880 --> 00:12:29,600
You could know him as the kid from Brooklyn or whatever.

279
00:12:29,600 --> 00:12:32,800
Or you could know him as Jay-Z, the mogul,

280
00:12:32,800 --> 00:12:35,120
the billionaire rapper or whatever.

281
00:12:35,120 --> 00:12:36,320
I don't know if he has a billion dollars,

282
00:12:36,320 --> 00:12:40,000
but close to a billion or a little more, I think.

283
00:12:40,000 --> 00:12:42,880
The simplest way, although this is a little contentious,

284
00:12:42,880 --> 00:12:46,240
to think of the sense or mode of presentation

285
00:12:46,240 --> 00:12:49,840
of a name or phrase is to think of it as a description.

286
00:12:49,840 --> 00:12:55,840
You could describe this guy as a billionaire music mogul

287
00:12:55,840 --> 00:12:59,520
or you could describe him as a middle-aged man

288
00:12:59,520 --> 00:13:00,960
who was born in Brooklyn

289
00:13:00,960 --> 00:13:03,760
and still lives most of the time in the greater New York area.

290
00:13:03,760 --> 00:13:06,880
Those are two different ways of presenting

291
00:13:06,880 --> 00:13:11,280
or characterizing this guy, Sean Carter or Jay-Z.

292
00:13:11,360 --> 00:13:13,040
Frege's point is this.

293
00:13:13,040 --> 00:13:16,400
A name, or for that matter, any other linguistic term,

294
00:13:17,120 --> 00:13:20,640
a name has not only this level of meaning,

295
00:13:20,640 --> 00:13:22,800
which is the object named,

296
00:13:22,800 --> 00:13:26,720
but also the way that that object is characterized

297
00:13:26,720 --> 00:13:30,560
or presented by the sign, by the name.

298
00:13:30,560 --> 00:13:32,640
Frege himself actually explains this,

299
00:13:32,640 --> 00:13:35,520
though with a somewhat abstract mathematical example

300
00:13:35,520 --> 00:13:38,640
that might not have been obvious from just reading the text.

301
00:13:38,640 --> 00:13:41,440
So I'm going to read it and then explain exactly what he means.

302
00:13:41,440 --> 00:13:45,680
Let ABC be the lines connecting the vertices of a triangle

303
00:13:45,680 --> 00:13:47,760
with the midpoints of the opposite sides.

304
00:13:47,760 --> 00:13:51,760
Okay, so there's no actual diagram in the published paper,

305
00:13:51,760 --> 00:13:54,320
but I created this diagram.

306
00:13:54,320 --> 00:13:56,880
You see that inside of this triangle, there are three lines.

307
00:13:56,880 --> 00:13:59,360
There's the vertical line, which is called A,

308
00:13:59,360 --> 00:14:02,080
and then there's this other line, that's line B,

309
00:14:02,080 --> 00:14:04,400
and then line C is the third line

310
00:14:04,400 --> 00:14:06,080
going from the lower right to the upper left.

311
00:14:06,080 --> 00:14:07,520
And the important thing to notice

312
00:14:07,520 --> 00:14:09,840
is that all three of these lines intersect,

313
00:14:09,840 --> 00:14:13,360
they cross each other or meet at the very same point in the middle.

314
00:14:13,360 --> 00:14:15,840
The point of intersection of A and B

315
00:14:15,840 --> 00:14:19,280
is then the same as the point of intersection of B and C.

316
00:14:19,280 --> 00:14:22,400
So there's just one point here in the middle of this diagram,

317
00:14:22,400 --> 00:14:25,040
but Frege mentions at least two different ways

318
00:14:25,040 --> 00:14:27,040
of describing that exact same point,

319
00:14:27,040 --> 00:14:30,000
the place where lines A and B intersect,

320
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:32,160
or you could describe the very same point

321
00:14:32,160 --> 00:14:35,200
as the place where lines B and C intersect.

322
00:14:35,200 --> 00:14:37,040
So we have different designations

323
00:14:37,040 --> 00:14:38,240
for the same point.

324
00:14:38,240 --> 00:14:41,040
And these names, point of intersection of A and B,

325
00:14:41,040 --> 00:14:42,960
point of intersection of B and C,

326
00:14:42,960 --> 00:14:45,840
likewise indicate the mode of presentation.

327
00:14:45,840 --> 00:14:48,240
So these two different names for the one point,

328
00:14:48,240 --> 00:14:50,960
the point of intersection of A and B,

329
00:14:50,960 --> 00:14:53,520
and the point of intersection of C and D,

330
00:14:53,520 --> 00:14:55,760
these two names, they pick out the same point,

331
00:14:55,760 --> 00:14:59,120
but they present that point in different ways.

332
00:14:59,120 --> 00:15:02,320
They involve different modes of presentation

333
00:15:02,320 --> 00:15:03,680
of that same point.

334
00:15:03,680 --> 00:15:06,480
And hence, the statement contains true knowledge.

335
00:15:06,480 --> 00:15:08,160
What he means by that is just that

336
00:15:08,160 --> 00:15:11,840
because these two different names for that one point

337
00:15:11,840 --> 00:15:14,400
have different modes of presentation,

338
00:15:14,400 --> 00:15:16,720
that sentence, the sentence that

339
00:15:16,720 --> 00:15:19,280
the point of intersection of A and B

340
00:15:19,280 --> 00:15:22,560
is the same as the point of intersection of B and C,

341
00:15:22,560 --> 00:15:25,360
that sentence, like sentence two here,

342
00:15:25,360 --> 00:15:28,400
can contain real genuine information,

343
00:15:28,400 --> 00:15:30,320
true knowledge, as Frege calls it.

344
00:15:30,320 --> 00:15:32,080
In our example, accordingly,

345
00:15:32,080 --> 00:15:33,760
the reference of the expressions

346
00:15:33,760 --> 00:15:35,600
the point of intersection of A and B

347
00:15:35,600 --> 00:15:37,840
and the point of intersection of B and C

348
00:15:37,840 --> 00:15:40,320
would be the same, but not their senses.

349
00:15:40,320 --> 00:15:44,320
Right, so these two names have the same referent,

350
00:15:44,320 --> 00:15:46,240
but different senses,

351
00:15:46,240 --> 00:15:48,480
different ways of presenting that referent.

352
00:15:48,480 --> 00:15:51,360
That's exactly what's going on with Sean Carter and Jay-Z.

353
00:15:51,360 --> 00:15:55,040
These two names, they refer to the same guy,

354
00:15:55,040 --> 00:15:56,480
they have the same referent,

355
00:15:56,480 --> 00:15:58,320
but they have different senses.

356
00:15:58,320 --> 00:16:00,880
They present him in different ways.

357
00:16:00,880 --> 00:16:02,800
And it's the same way with the example

358
00:16:02,800 --> 00:16:04,800
of the morning star and the evening star.

359
00:16:04,800 --> 00:16:07,360
The referent of evening star would be the same

360
00:16:07,360 --> 00:16:09,840
as that of morning star, but not the sense.

361
00:16:09,840 --> 00:16:13,520
So those two names, the morning star and the evening star,

362
00:16:13,520 --> 00:16:15,280
they have the same referent,

363
00:16:15,280 --> 00:16:16,640
which happens to be Venus,

364
00:16:16,640 --> 00:16:19,360
but they present that referent differently.

365
00:16:19,360 --> 00:16:23,600
They make reference to Venus via different senses.

366
00:16:23,600 --> 00:16:26,240
And this theory, this theory that says

367
00:16:26,240 --> 00:16:28,480
that for all the linguistic signs,

368
00:16:28,480 --> 00:16:30,400
there are two levels of meaning,

369
00:16:30,400 --> 00:16:32,640
the level of sense and the level of reference.

370
00:16:32,720 --> 00:16:36,160
This theory can explain both of these facts

371
00:16:36,160 --> 00:16:38,320
about identity statements like two.

372
00:16:38,320 --> 00:16:41,200
It can explain why these sentences are informative

373
00:16:41,200 --> 00:16:43,280
and it can explain why that information

374
00:16:43,280 --> 00:16:45,520
can be non-linguistic and empirical.

375
00:16:45,520 --> 00:16:47,200
It's possible for one to already know

376
00:16:47,200 --> 00:16:49,360
the linguistic information.

377
00:16:49,360 --> 00:16:53,040
One knows the sense of Sean Carter, the meaning.

378
00:16:53,040 --> 00:16:57,360
And one knows the sense of the term or name Jay-Z.

379
00:16:57,360 --> 00:17:00,080
But then one can find out, oh!

380
00:17:00,080 --> 00:17:01,040
Oh!

381
00:17:01,040 --> 00:17:04,080
These two terms that I already know the meaning to,

382
00:17:04,080 --> 00:17:06,320
they refer to the very same guy.

383
00:17:06,320 --> 00:17:08,320
That is how Frege solves the puzzle.

384
00:17:08,320 --> 00:17:10,560
Oh, but there's more, there's like way more.

385
00:17:10,560 --> 00:17:13,280
The regular connection between a sign, its sense

386
00:17:13,280 --> 00:17:15,200
and its referent is of such a kind

387
00:17:15,200 --> 00:17:18,080
that to the sign, there corresponds a definite sense

388
00:17:18,080 --> 00:17:20,560
and to that, in turn, a definite referent.

389
00:17:20,560 --> 00:17:22,880
The point Frege is making there is just that

390
00:17:22,880 --> 00:17:27,200
in the normal case, for one name, there is one sense

391
00:17:27,200 --> 00:17:30,000
and then one referent, one to one to one.

392
00:17:30,080 --> 00:17:32,560
While to a given referent, an object,

393
00:17:32,560 --> 00:17:35,040
there does not belong only a single sign.

394
00:17:35,040 --> 00:17:38,480
But if instead we start with the object, the referent,

395
00:17:38,480 --> 00:17:41,600
there might be more than one name for that object, right?

396
00:17:41,600 --> 00:17:44,640
There might be Jay-Z and Sean Carter and Hove.

397
00:17:45,200 --> 00:17:46,480
That's another one, I think.

398
00:17:46,480 --> 00:17:48,720
The same sense has different expressions

399
00:17:48,720 --> 00:17:51,280
in different languages or even in the same language.

400
00:17:51,280 --> 00:17:52,880
Okay, this is an additional point,

401
00:17:52,880 --> 00:17:55,920
but Frege thinks that the same sense

402
00:17:55,920 --> 00:17:58,480
can be the meaning of different terms.

403
00:17:58,560 --> 00:18:01,600
It might be, I'm sort of playing a little fast

404
00:18:01,600 --> 00:18:05,200
and loose here, but it might be that Jay-Z

405
00:18:05,200 --> 00:18:08,640
and Hove, H-O-V, I'm pretty sure that's how it's spelled,

406
00:18:08,640 --> 00:18:10,240
those are two different names,

407
00:18:10,240 --> 00:18:12,560
but maybe they present him in the same way.

408
00:18:12,560 --> 00:18:15,600
So they have the same sense, two different names,

409
00:18:15,600 --> 00:18:17,120
same sense, same referent.

410
00:18:17,120 --> 00:18:19,120
That's also possible, Frege thinks.

411
00:18:19,120 --> 00:18:21,680
And then there's the case of what are today

412
00:18:21,680 --> 00:18:23,520
commonly called empty names.

413
00:18:23,520 --> 00:18:26,400
These are names that are meaningful,

414
00:18:26,400 --> 00:18:28,400
but they don't refer to anything.

415
00:18:28,400 --> 00:18:30,960
It may perhaps be granted that every grammatically

416
00:18:30,960 --> 00:18:33,920
well-formed expression representing a proper name

417
00:18:33,920 --> 00:18:35,520
always has a sense.

418
00:18:35,520 --> 00:18:38,400
This just means that if a name is meaningful,

419
00:18:38,400 --> 00:18:39,520
it has a sense.

420
00:18:39,520 --> 00:18:41,920
But this is not to say that to the sense,

421
00:18:41,920 --> 00:18:43,840
there also corresponds a referent.

422
00:18:43,840 --> 00:18:47,200
But just because a name is meaningful and has a sense

423
00:18:47,200 --> 00:18:49,920
doesn't mean that there really is an object in the world

424
00:18:49,920 --> 00:18:52,480
that is referred to by that name.

