523
00:23:12,480 --> 00:23:14,240
No one else can come and look at those.

524
00:23:14,240 --> 00:23:15,600
The purpose of this analogy

525
00:23:15,600 --> 00:23:17,920
is just to explain how all of these things,

526
00:23:17,920 --> 00:23:19,280
the referent, the sense,

527
00:23:19,280 --> 00:23:21,600
and the conception are related to one another.

528
00:23:21,600 --> 00:23:24,080
Frege actually doesn't care about mental stuff,

529
00:23:24,080 --> 00:23:26,320
like your associated mental conception

530
00:23:26,320 --> 00:23:27,760
or experience or whatever.

531
00:23:27,760 --> 00:23:29,760
This is irrelevant really.

532
00:23:29,760 --> 00:23:32,080
When he's talking about the meanings of terms,

533
00:23:32,080 --> 00:23:34,720
he's just talking about the sense and the reference.

534
00:23:34,720 --> 00:23:38,000
But he has to mention all of this stuff about conception

535
00:23:38,000 --> 00:23:40,480
just so that his readers don't accidentally

536
00:23:40,480 --> 00:23:43,120
or mistakenly think that when he talks about sense,

537
00:23:43,120 --> 00:23:45,440
he's talking about some private mental thing,

538
00:23:45,440 --> 00:23:47,680
he's clarifying that that's not what he's talking about.

539
00:23:49,200 --> 00:23:50,960
Okay, now things get real.

540
00:23:52,480 --> 00:23:53,360
Up to this point,

541
00:23:53,360 --> 00:23:55,360
we've only been talking about names

542
00:23:55,360 --> 00:23:57,440
or maybe subject expressions,

543
00:23:57,440 --> 00:23:57,760
whatever.

544
00:23:57,760 --> 00:24:00,080
We weren't talking about whole sentences.

545
00:24:00,080 --> 00:24:03,520
Now, Frege is going to start talking about the sense

546
00:24:03,520 --> 00:24:05,200
and the reference of whole sentences,

547
00:24:05,200 --> 00:24:08,560
like Sean Carter is rich or Jay-Z is rich.

548
00:24:10,000 --> 00:24:12,560
The thing you have to absolutely understand

549
00:24:12,560 --> 00:24:15,360
in order to understand what happens in this part of the paper

550
00:24:15,360 --> 00:24:17,600
is the idea of compositionality.

551
00:24:17,600 --> 00:24:20,560
I have a whole other video explaining compositionality

552
00:24:20,560 --> 00:24:21,920
and if you haven't watched that,

553
00:24:21,920 --> 00:24:24,160
you got to go watch it, link in the description.

554
00:24:24,160 --> 00:24:26,800
But very briefly, the idea is this.

555
00:24:26,800 --> 00:24:30,480
The meaning of a whole sentence is composed of

556
00:24:30,480 --> 00:24:34,560
or built up out of the meanings of the individual parts.

557
00:24:34,560 --> 00:24:37,760
So the meaning of this sentence, Jay-Z is rich,

558
00:24:37,760 --> 00:24:40,720
is made up out of the meaning of Jay-Z,

559
00:24:40,720 --> 00:24:43,200
the meaning of is, and the meaning of rich.

560
00:24:43,200 --> 00:24:44,240
You put those together,

561
00:24:44,240 --> 00:24:45,360
there's some rules for that,

562
00:24:45,360 --> 00:24:47,440
and you get the meaning of the whole sentence.

563
00:24:47,440 --> 00:24:49,120
This is a fact about language,

564
00:24:49,120 --> 00:24:51,440
and Frege takes it very seriously.

565
00:24:51,440 --> 00:24:54,160
He thinks that compositionality is operating

566
00:24:54,160 --> 00:24:57,200
at both the level of sense and reference.

567
00:24:57,200 --> 00:25:01,040
If terms, if linguistic terms have sort of two levels of meaning,

568
00:25:01,040 --> 00:25:03,840
they have the level of sense and the level of reference,

569
00:25:03,840 --> 00:25:08,800
then those, the sense bits are all going to add up together

570
00:25:08,880 --> 00:25:11,680
to give you the sense of a whole sentence.

571
00:25:11,680 --> 00:25:15,120
And also, all the references are going to add up together

572
00:25:15,120 --> 00:25:17,520
to give you the reference of a whole sentence.

573
00:25:17,520 --> 00:25:19,840
So what he's trying to do in this part of the paper,

574
00:25:19,840 --> 00:25:21,040
the middle of the paper,

575
00:25:21,040 --> 00:25:22,640
is he's trying to figure out,

576
00:25:22,640 --> 00:25:24,880
okay, I've already basically said

577
00:25:24,880 --> 00:25:28,080
what the sense and reference of like a name is,

578
00:25:28,080 --> 00:25:30,800
what's the sense and reference of a whole sentence?

579
00:25:30,800 --> 00:25:34,320
And he's constrained in his answer to that question

580
00:25:34,320 --> 00:25:35,760
by compositionality.

581
00:25:35,760 --> 00:25:39,040
The only thing that could be the sense of a sentence

582
00:25:39,040 --> 00:25:41,280
is something that could be made up out of

583
00:25:41,280 --> 00:25:44,320
the senses of those individual words or terms.

584
00:25:44,320 --> 00:25:46,240
And the only thing that could be the reference

585
00:25:46,240 --> 00:25:48,080
of a whole sentence is something

586
00:25:48,080 --> 00:25:49,920
that could be made up out of

587
00:25:49,920 --> 00:25:53,200
the references of all the individual words or terms.

588
00:25:53,200 --> 00:25:55,600
The first thing that Frege considers

589
00:25:55,600 --> 00:25:57,840
as a possible sense or reference

590
00:25:57,840 --> 00:25:59,920
of a whole declarative sentence

591
00:25:59,920 --> 00:26:02,240
is what today we call a proposition.

592
00:26:02,240 --> 00:26:04,080
Frege doesn't call it a proposition,

593
00:26:04,080 --> 00:26:05,600
he calls it a thought.

594
00:26:05,600 --> 00:26:07,200
Now, that's confusing because normally

595
00:26:07,200 --> 00:26:08,080
when you think of thought,

596
00:26:08,080 --> 00:26:09,760
you think of a private mental thing,

597
00:26:09,760 --> 00:26:11,680
and that's not what Frege is talking about here.

598
00:26:11,680 --> 00:26:13,200
When he says thought,

599
00:26:13,200 --> 00:26:18,160
he means the publicly available meaning of a sentence.

600
00:26:18,160 --> 00:26:20,320
Is this thought now to be regarded

601
00:26:20,320 --> 00:26:22,240
as its sense or its reference?

602
00:26:22,240 --> 00:26:23,680
So the question is,

603
00:26:23,680 --> 00:26:27,520
is the proposition or the thought associated with a sentence,

604
00:26:27,520 --> 00:26:29,360
is that the sense of the sentence

605
00:26:29,360 --> 00:26:31,360
or the reference of the sentence?

606
00:26:31,360 --> 00:26:33,120
Let us assume for the time being

607
00:26:33,120 --> 00:26:34,720
that the sentence has a reference.

608
00:26:34,720 --> 00:26:37,600
If we now replace one word of the sentence by another,

609
00:26:37,600 --> 00:26:38,800
having the same reference,

610
00:26:38,800 --> 00:26:40,160
but a different sense,

611
00:26:40,160 --> 00:26:41,760
this can have no influence

612
00:26:41,760 --> 00:26:43,440
upon the reference of the sentence.

613
00:26:43,440 --> 00:26:46,240
Ah, so Frege has found a little test

614
00:26:46,240 --> 00:26:48,240
to tell whether the proposition

615
00:26:48,240 --> 00:26:49,680
or the thought or whatever

616
00:26:49,680 --> 00:26:51,920
is the sense of the sentence or the reference.

617
00:26:51,920 --> 00:26:54,480
He realizes that there are these terms,

618
00:26:54,480 --> 00:26:56,160
Sean Carter and Jay-Z,

619
00:26:56,160 --> 00:26:58,080
which have different senses,

620
00:26:58,080 --> 00:26:59,200
but the same reference.

621
00:26:59,200 --> 00:27:01,280
And so if you switch between the two,

622
00:27:01,280 --> 00:27:03,920
if you swap out this name,

623
00:27:04,000 --> 00:27:04,880
Sean Carter,

624
00:27:04,880 --> 00:27:06,960
and you put in this name Jay-Z

625
00:27:06,960 --> 00:27:08,080
into the same sentence,

626
00:27:08,080 --> 00:27:09,840
that's the difference between three and four,

627
00:27:09,840 --> 00:27:11,280
if you swap them out

628
00:27:11,280 --> 00:27:14,240
because these two names have the same reference,

629
00:27:15,040 --> 00:27:17,600
then switching between these two sentences

630
00:27:17,600 --> 00:27:20,320
should not change the reference of the whole sentence,

631
00:27:20,320 --> 00:27:22,800
but it should change at least sometimes

632
00:27:22,800 --> 00:27:24,560
the sense of these sentences.

633
00:27:24,560 --> 00:27:26,160
We're just switching out two terms.

634
00:27:26,160 --> 00:27:28,560
We're going from a term with one sense

635
00:27:28,560 --> 00:27:29,920
to a term with a different sense.

636
00:27:29,920 --> 00:27:31,360
So these two sentences

637
00:27:31,360 --> 00:27:32,960
should have different senses.

638
00:27:32,960 --> 00:27:36,320
But because these two names have the same reference,

639
00:27:36,320 --> 00:27:39,040
these two sentences should have the same reference.

640
00:27:39,040 --> 00:27:40,880
Frege is trying to figure out

641
00:27:40,880 --> 00:27:42,560
whether or not the proposition

642
00:27:42,560 --> 00:27:45,280
or the thought expressed by a sentence

643
00:27:45,280 --> 00:27:46,880
is the sense or the reference.

644
00:27:46,880 --> 00:27:48,720
Well, there's this constraint.

645
00:27:49,360 --> 00:27:51,040
These two sentences

646
00:27:51,040 --> 00:27:53,680
will have different senses,

647
00:27:53,680 --> 00:27:55,600
but the same reference.

648
00:27:55,600 --> 00:27:58,000
Yet we can see that in such a case,

649
00:27:58,000 --> 00:27:59,600
the thought changes.

650
00:27:59,600 --> 00:28:02,480
Frege notices that these two sentences

651
00:28:03,120 --> 00:28:04,800
express different propositions.

652
00:28:04,800 --> 00:28:06,480
They express different thoughts.

653
00:28:06,480 --> 00:28:10,320
So the thought cannot be the reference of a name

654
00:28:10,320 --> 00:28:12,560
because the thought changes between these two,

655
00:28:12,560 --> 00:28:14,080
but the reference can't change

656
00:28:14,080 --> 00:28:17,600
because this name has the same reference as this name,

657
00:28:17,600 --> 00:28:19,360
this has the same reference as this.

658
00:28:19,360 --> 00:28:21,280
These are referentially the same.

659
00:28:21,280 --> 00:28:22,880
So if something changes,

660
00:28:22,880 --> 00:28:23,840
if the thought changes,

661
00:28:23,840 --> 00:28:25,680
then the thought has to be the sense,

662
00:28:25,680 --> 00:28:26,880
not the reference.

663
00:28:26,880 --> 00:28:28,160
The thought, accordingly,

664
00:28:28,160 --> 00:28:30,240
cannot be the reference of the sentence,

665
00:28:30,240 --> 00:28:32,640
but must rather be considered as the sense.

666
00:28:32,640 --> 00:28:34,160
Okay, so having figured out

667
00:28:34,160 --> 00:28:36,160
what the sense of a whole sentence is,

668
00:28:36,160 --> 00:28:38,080
it's the proposition expressed by that sentence,

669
00:28:38,080 --> 00:28:40,160
the next question is, well, what's the reference?

670
00:28:40,160 --> 00:28:42,560
What is the reference of a declarative sentence

671
00:28:42,560 --> 00:28:44,240
like this or like this?

672
00:28:44,240 --> 00:28:45,600
Sean Carter is rich.

673
00:28:45,600 --> 00:28:46,560
Jay-Z is rich.

674
00:28:46,560 --> 00:28:48,400
We know what these names refer to.

675
00:28:48,400 --> 00:28:50,000
They refer to the guy.

676
00:28:50,000 --> 00:28:52,080
What do the whole sentences refer to?

677
00:28:52,080 --> 00:28:53,760
And once again, when figuring this out,

678
00:28:53,760 --> 00:28:56,320
Frege is constrained by compositionality.

679
00:28:56,320 --> 00:28:58,560
Whatever this thing the reference is,

680
00:28:58,560 --> 00:29:01,920
it's gonna have to somehow be built up out of

681
00:29:01,920 --> 00:29:04,320
the references of all the individual parts.

682
00:29:04,320 --> 00:29:06,640
And this gives Frege an argument

683
00:29:06,640 --> 00:29:09,760
for why the reference of a declarative sentence like this

684
00:29:09,760 --> 00:29:11,840
is that sentence's truth value.

685
00:29:12,960 --> 00:29:15,200
The truth value of a declarative sentence

686
00:29:15,200 --> 00:29:17,520
is just whether or not the sentence is true or false.

687
00:29:17,520 --> 00:29:19,280
There's two possible truth values.

688
00:29:19,840 --> 00:29:21,680
True is one of them, false is the other.

689
00:29:21,680 --> 00:29:23,680
You know, this sentence, Jay-Z is rich.

690
00:29:23,680 --> 00:29:24,400
That's true.

691
00:29:24,400 --> 00:29:26,080
Its truth value is true.

692
00:29:26,080 --> 00:29:30,160
So Frege thinks that this whole sentence

693
00:29:30,240 --> 00:29:33,520
refers to truth or the true.

694
00:29:33,520 --> 00:29:34,880
That's what it refers to.

695
00:29:34,880 --> 00:29:36,880
Okay, weird, but he has an argument

696
00:29:36,880 --> 00:29:39,200
for why he thinks this has to be the case.

697
00:29:39,200 --> 00:29:41,680
The reference of a whole declarative sentence

698
00:29:41,680 --> 00:29:43,440
has to be composed up

699
00:29:43,440 --> 00:29:45,840
out of the references of the individual parts.

700
00:29:45,840 --> 00:29:47,920
Therefore, any change in the reference

701
00:29:47,920 --> 00:29:49,600
of any of the individual parts

702
00:29:49,600 --> 00:29:53,200
must result in a change in the reference of the whole sentence.

703
00:29:53,200 --> 00:29:55,520
And whenever there is not a change

704
00:29:55,520 --> 00:29:57,360
in the reference of the individual parts,

705
00:29:57,360 --> 00:29:59,680
like when switching between three and four,

706
00:29:59,680 --> 00:30:01,600
the references of all of these parts,

707
00:30:01,600 --> 00:30:04,080
this name, this, this, this name, this, this,

708
00:30:04,080 --> 00:30:06,320
the references of all this stays the same

709
00:30:06,320 --> 00:30:07,760
when you switch from three to four.

710
00:30:07,760 --> 00:30:09,920
So the reference of these whole sentences

711
00:30:09,920 --> 00:30:11,200
has to stay the same.

712
00:30:11,200 --> 00:30:13,280
Therefore, whatever the references

713
00:30:13,280 --> 00:30:15,040
of these declarative sentences are,

714
00:30:15,040 --> 00:30:16,240
they have to be the same.

715
00:30:16,240 --> 00:30:19,280
These two sentences have to have the same reference

716
00:30:19,280 --> 00:30:21,840
because all of their parts have the same reference

717
00:30:21,840 --> 00:30:24,000
because Sean Carter and Jay-Z

718
00:30:24,000 --> 00:30:26,400
are two different names with the same reference.

719
00:30:26,400 --> 00:30:29,520
These two names are what's called co-referring terms.

720
00:30:29,600 --> 00:30:31,040
Co-referring terms.

721
00:30:31,040 --> 00:30:32,400
Co-referring terms.

722
00:30:32,400 --> 00:30:34,160
They refer to the same thing.

723
00:30:34,160 --> 00:30:36,880
And so this test that Frege has come up with is,

724
00:30:36,880 --> 00:30:40,240
oh, well, if you swap out one term

725
00:30:40,240 --> 00:30:42,560
for another term that's co-referring,

726
00:30:42,560 --> 00:30:45,280
right, if you go from sentence three to sentence four,

727
00:30:45,280 --> 00:30:46,800
if you do this swap,

728
00:30:46,800 --> 00:30:49,120
you have to always preserve

729
00:30:49,120 --> 00:30:50,720
the reference of the whole sentence.

730
00:30:50,720 --> 00:30:53,040
So then the question for Frege is very simple.

731
00:30:53,040 --> 00:30:55,280
What is something about these sentences

732
00:30:55,280 --> 00:30:57,360
that always stays the same

733
00:30:57,360 --> 00:31:00,080
whenever you swap out co-referring terms?

734
00:31:00,080 --> 00:31:02,080
Whenever you go from a sentence like three

735
00:31:02,080 --> 00:31:03,520
to a sentence like four,

736
00:31:03,520 --> 00:31:05,760
what stays the same every time?

737
00:31:05,760 --> 00:31:07,280
Well, it's not the thought.

738
00:31:07,280 --> 00:31:09,120
It's not the cognitive value.

739
00:31:09,120 --> 00:31:10,160
The thought changes.

740
00:31:10,160 --> 00:31:11,760
That's the sense and that changes.

741
00:31:11,760 --> 00:31:13,040
It's the truth value.

742
00:31:13,040 --> 00:31:16,800
Whenever you swap in a different name for this guy,

743
00:31:16,800 --> 00:31:19,440
the resulting sentence will always have

744
00:31:19,440 --> 00:31:22,080
the same truth value as these two.

745
00:31:23,360 --> 00:31:24,960
And there it is, hove.

746
00:31:24,960 --> 00:31:26,000
Hove is rich.

747
00:31:26,000 --> 00:31:27,200
That's true as well.

748
00:31:27,200 --> 00:31:29,680
This is true, this is true, and this is true.

749
00:31:29,680 --> 00:31:31,920
You're never gonna be able to get a sentence

750
00:31:31,920 --> 00:31:34,560
that just switches in a co-referring term here

751
00:31:34,560 --> 00:31:36,480
and all of a sudden that sentence is false

752
00:31:36,480 --> 00:31:38,000
whereas all of these remain true.

753
00:31:38,000 --> 00:31:39,120
You're never gonna get that

754
00:31:39,120 --> 00:31:41,920
because the truth value always stays the same

755
00:31:41,920 --> 00:31:43,920
when you swap in co-referring terms

756
00:31:43,920 --> 00:31:45,360
and that is Frege's argument

757
00:31:45,360 --> 00:31:48,160
for why the truth value of a declarative sentence

758
00:31:48,160 --> 00:31:50,400
is the reference of that sentence.

759
00:31:50,400 --> 00:31:53,360
And the same would hold if these sentences were false, right?

760
00:31:53,360 --> 00:31:56,080
If instead of saying Sean Carter is rich,

761
00:31:56,080 --> 00:31:58,800
this sentence said Sean Carter is enshrined

762
00:31:58,800 --> 00:32:01,040
in the country music hall of fame,

763
00:32:01,040 --> 00:32:02,720
well then three would be false

764
00:32:02,720 --> 00:32:05,120
but then the same sentence where you swap in Jay-Z,

765
00:32:05,120 --> 00:32:06,560
that would also be false.

766
00:32:06,560 --> 00:32:08,080
Hove would also be false.

767
00:32:08,080 --> 00:32:11,280
Any sentence that is false of Sean Carter

768
00:32:11,280 --> 00:32:14,160
is also false of Jay-Z, is also false of Hove.

769
00:32:14,160 --> 00:32:17,120
Swapping out these names with different senses

770
00:32:17,120 --> 00:32:20,560
but the same reference changes the thought or proposition

771
00:32:20,560 --> 00:32:22,640
but never changes the truth value.

772
00:32:22,640 --> 00:32:24,240
At least that's true in the case

773
00:32:24,240 --> 00:32:25,840
of simple sentences like this.

774
00:32:25,920 --> 00:32:28,480
More complex sentences with like quotations

775
00:32:28,480 --> 00:32:29,920
and things like that, this won't work

776
00:32:29,920 --> 00:32:31,760
but we're not gonna worry about that now.

777
00:32:31,760 --> 00:32:34,960
Let's just read Frege's argument for this conclusion.

778
00:32:34,960 --> 00:32:37,280
If our supposition that the reference of a sentence

779
00:32:37,280 --> 00:32:39,200
is its truth value is correct,

780
00:32:39,200 --> 00:32:40,960
the latter, that is the truth value,

781
00:32:40,960 --> 00:32:42,640
must remain unchanged

782
00:32:42,640 --> 00:32:44,480
when a part of the sentence is replaced

783
00:32:44,480 --> 00:32:46,800
by an expression having the same reference

784
00:32:46,800 --> 00:32:48,400
and this is in fact the case.

785
00:32:48,400 --> 00:32:50,720
Right, cool, that's just what we were saying.

786
00:32:50,720 --> 00:32:52,000
Leibniz explains,

787
00:32:52,960 --> 00:33:00,080
That's my best shot pronouncing the Latin.

788
00:33:00,080 --> 00:33:03,120
It means equal are those which for each other

789
00:33:03,120 --> 00:33:05,920
mutually substituted can be saving the truth.

790
00:33:05,920 --> 00:33:08,400
And what that means in comprehensible English

791
00:33:08,400 --> 00:33:10,000
is just that what it is to say

792
00:33:10,000 --> 00:33:11,840
that two things are the same thing

793
00:33:11,840 --> 00:33:14,080
